{"by":"mikae1","id":47761226,"kids":[47771259,47761231],"parent":47760529,"text":"This was bound to happen. I&#x27;ve edited stills in Resolve for years thinking this day would come. Resolve has supported DNG raw files (as long as they&#x27;re not converted from funky sensors such as Fujifilm X-trans). But, it was always a bit of a hack.<p>Kind of stoked to see this release even though I&#x27;ve transitioned to a 100% open source photo workflow on Linux now.<p>IMO, most exciting developments in photo editing today happens in open source. But this is really something.","time":1776140676,"type":"comment"}